Two congressmen urged President Reaganto to call congressional leaders to a domestic economic summitto settle budget and trade matters they said contributed to thestock market fall.    Noting the nosediving New York Stock Exchange, Rep DavidObey, a Wisconsin Democrat and former chairman of theCongressional Economic Committee, said "for the last five yearsthis economic recovery has been running on borrowed money andborrowed time."    In another House speech, Democrat Donald Pease of Ohio saida domestic economic summit was "desperately needed." Reuter&#3;